What you need to know:  She said the event will go a long way in helping the continental heal from the effects of the Covid-19 pandemic. Initially, the competition was scheduled for 2020, but the pandemic led to its postponement.“Sporting activities build character and have been a key feature in keeping our human spirit alive during a crisis. As we embark on re-energising our continent from the effects of the Covid-19 pandemic, events such as these Games will serve us well.” said the First Lady.